ew York, in the 1960s. Chasing excellence on both the gridiron and in the courtroom, however, would require resilience in ways he could not have imagined.As A View from Two Benches shows us, Bob Thomas reached the top of two separate and distinct professions, guided by a bedrock of faith that has impacted his decisions and actions as both a football player and a judge, helping him navigate the peaks and valleys of life. As Doug Feldmann reveals, Bob Thomas has always stayed true to the values he learned in his earliest days.Doug Feldmann's rich biography of an accomplished kicker and a proud justice of the law shows us that determination and resilience go a long way to a successful and impactful life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aFootball playerszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aJudgeszIllinoisvBiography. 4aMidwest. 4aSports & Games. 7aSPORTS & RECREATION / Football.2bisacsh  aBob Thomas, Chicago Bears, American football, Justice Robert Thomas, Notre Dame, NFL, Illinois Supreme Court.1 aDitka, Mike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069046008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2020 Englishz978311070486008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2020z9783110704587oZDB-23-DGC40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501750007?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501750007423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501750007/original  a978-3-11-069046-0  Cornell University Press Compl